      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KEAYANG STUKA (4) continues to race well with top-four results in his three outings here since a fresh win at Bendigo. Drew one sport wider than than this when he missed by just a head here last week. That performance suggested he may be ready for a return to to the winners' stall. ROCKINWITHATTITUDE (6) has had seven weeks off since adding another Group 1 to her resume, beating the mares in the Macarthur Mile at Menangle. Had won two of her previous four attempts here and has been kept up to the mark with a couple of trials so can continue the strong form. MECARNO (2) has won a trial since his midfield return so should have come on and races very well second-up with two wins and a placing from three tries. Has won four of six attempts at this circuit and distance and draws for a better result. It's been a while since we've seen ARCEE PHOENIX (5) produce his best but he'll be fitter second-up so look for improvement.",
